description: It was the pair's first event together since they became the GOP's nominees at the Republican National Convention in Milwaukee.
title: Trump holds first rally with running mate JD Vance

description: Saturday marks 55 years since the crew of Apollo 11 landed on the moon. Buzz Aldrin, the only surviving member of that crew, remembered the historic moment by writing, "I am still inspired by what we all saw and did, the best of America and the best of humanity."
title: U.S. celebrates 55th anniversary of Apollo 11 moon landing

description: The U.S. Navy this week posthumously exonerated 50 Black sailors who were wrongly punished in connection with the 1944 explosion in Port Chicago, California, which killed 320 people and injured hundreds more. Elizabeth Cook has more.
title: Navy exonerates Black sailors 80 years after Port Chicago disaster

description: Israel said it carried out airstrikes Saturday on a city in Yemen controlled by the Houthi militant group. The airstrikes came one day after the Iranian-backed Houthis claimed responsible for a  drone attack in Tel Aviv. Debora Patta reports.
title: Israel carries out airstrikes in Yemen following Tel Aviv attack

description: Democratic Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee of Texas, who served in Congress for nearly three decades, has died at the age of 74. A champion for progressive causes, Jackson Lee led efforts to make Juneteenth a national holiday.
title: Sheila Jackson Lee, longtime Texas congresswoman, dies at 74

description: President Donald Trump and his new running mate, Sen. JD Vance, were holding a campaign rally in the battleground state of Michigan Saturday. With Saturday's event, the Trump campaign is signaling their path to victory runs through the Midwest. Caitlin Huey-Burns reports.
title: Trump, Vance hold first joint campaign rally

description: Here's a look at the top stories making headlines on the "CBS Weekend News" with Adriana Diaz.
title: "CBS Weekend News" headlines for Saturday, July 20, 2024

description: Gov. Chris Sununu signed the bill Friday, saying in a statement it "ensures fairness and safety in women's sports by maintaining integrity and competitive balance in athletic competitions."
title: New Hampshire governor signs bill banning transgender girls from girls' sports

description: Sandra Hemme, whose murder conviction was overturned after she served 43 years in prison, is now free — despite objections from Missouri's attorney general.
title: Missouri woman who spent 43 years in prison is free

description: Recovery continues after global computer outage; Otter who terrorized California surfers returns.
title: 7/20: Saturday Morning

description: Al-Masirah TV, a media outlet controlled by Houthi rebels in Yemen reported the airstrikes in the port city of Hodeidah.
title: Israeli military airstrikes hit Houthi targets in Yemen after attacks

description: A former classmate told CBS News that Thomas Matthew Crooks, the man who shot former President Donald Trump, tried out for Bethel Park High School's varsity rifle team.
title: Trump gunman's school says he did not try out for rifle team

description: Check in to the Pennzoil 250 NASCAR Xfinity Series race today, even if you cut the cord and don't have cable.
title: How to watch the Pennzoil 250 NASCAR race today

description: Michelin-star chef Niklas Ekstedt uses ancient Scandinavian methods to create stunning contemporary dishes. That means no gas or electricity, resulting in a unique culinary experience. Dana Jacobson has more.
title: How a renowned chef uses ancient cooking techniques to create a unique experience

description: The war in Gaza, sparked by Hamas' Oct. 7 attack on southern Israel, has killed more than 38,900 people, according to the territory's Health Ministry.
title: Israeli airstrikes kill at least 13 people in Gaza refugee camp

description: Police in Bangladesh have enacted a strict curfew with a "shoot-on-sight" order amid violent protests and chaos.
title: U.S. State Department raises travel advisory for Bangladesh amid unrest

description: The USS Dwight D. Eisenhower and its 4,000 sailors returned from a nine-month deployment in the Red Sea this week. While overseas, the carrier group spent much of its time defending shipping lanes from attacks from Iranian-backed Yemeni rebels and taking part in some of the most intense air combat since World War II.
title: Aircraft carrier returns after nine months defending Red Sea shipping routes

description: Acclaimed singer-songwriter Amos Lee returns to Saturday Sessions. The Philadelphia native known for his soulful voice worked as a teacher and bartender before giving music a try - and now, two decades later, Lee has recorded 10 studio albums. An eleventh album is set to be released next month, ahead of a tour with the Indigo Girls in the fall. Now, from his new album "Transmissions," here is Amos Lee with "Hold On Tight."
title: Saturday Sessions: Amos Lee performs "Hold On Tight"

description: A live album recorded by Louis Armstrong three years before his death in 1971 has been released. It's another moment in the spotlight for the beloved musician. Michelle Miller has more.
title: New Louis Armstrong live album, recorded in 1968, released

description: The German-based sportswear company drew criticism from Israel for including supermodel Bella Hadid in the advertising for the SL72 shoes.
title: Adidas apologizes for Bella Hadid ad linked to 1972 Munich Olympics

description: Birdwatching might seem like an antiquated activity - but thanks to young fans and TikTok, it's having a moment in the spotlight. Actor Ian Harding detailed his love for the hobby in a new memoir, "Odd Birds."
title: Actor Ian Harding talks birdwatching and new memoir

description: Otter 841 terrorized surfers in Santa Cruz, California last year, biting and hijacking boards. Multiple operations to capture her failed, and she disappeared without notice in October. Now, she's back. Surfers are on the lookout while experts try to explain her odd behavior.
title: Otter who terrorized California surfers returns

description: Acclaimed singer-songwriter Amos Lee returns to Saturday Sessions. The Philadelphia native known for his soulful voice worked as a teacher and bartender before giving music a try - and now, two decades later, Lee has recorded 10 studio albums. description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken said that negotiations to bring about a ceasefire in Gaza are "nearing the 10-yard line." Meanwhile, the International Court of Justice issued a historic ruling declaring that the Israeli occupation of Palestinian territories since 1967 has been illegal.
title: Blinken says ceasefire negotiations in Gaza are advancing

description: Dangerous heat has posed a threat around the world this year.
title: Lightning strikes in Greece start fires, kill cattle amid heat wave

description: According to NOAA, last month was the hottest June on record globally, and sea temperatures stayed well above average. The hotter-than-usual ocean water is a cause for concern for delicate coral reefs. In Florida, a group of veterans is working to help restore the vital ecosystems — and it's helping more than just the reefs.
title: Veterans group works to restore coral reefs

description: Police say a Florida man accused of making threats against former President Donald Trump, U.S. Sen. JD Vance and their families on social media has been arrested.
title: Florida man arrested, accused of making threats against Trump, Vance on social media

description: AI bots like Google AI have given incorrect information, with the results ranging from humorous to potentially dangerous.
title: Software developers want AI to give medical advice. But how accurate is it?

description: With medical providers facing rising levels of burnout, software designers are testing specialized AI-powered chatbots that they hope provide preventative care advice to patients. However, CBS News Confirmed found that the summaries given from existing AI bots like ChatGPT aren't always accurate.
title: Software providers test healthcare AI bots, but are they accurate?

description: The Secret Service is under intense scrutiny following the attempted assassination of former President Donald Trump last weekend. Agency director Kimberly Cheatle is set to testify before a Congressional committee on Monday. Meanwhile, a funeral was held for the rallygoer killed in the shooting.
title: Secret Service scrutiny continues after Trump assassination attempt

description: On this edition of CBS Mornings Deals, Adriane Kiss shows us items that might just become essentials in your everyday life. Visit cbsdeals.com to take advantage of these exclusive deals today. CBS earns commissions on purchases made through cbsdeals.com.
title: Exclusive discounts from CBS Mornings Deals

description: Congresswoman Sheila Jackson Lee has died at 74 after a battle with pancreatic cancer. Meanwhile, cracking ice on a lake in Chile is producing unique, echoing sounds. All that and all that matters in today’s Eye Opener.
title: Eye Opener: Congresswoman Sheila Jackson Lee dies

description: A Russian court sentenced Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich to 16 years in a maximum-security prison. He was convicted of espionage charges in what the U.S. government has denounced as a sham trial. The White House says it is continuing to push for his release.
title: Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich convicted in Russia

description: President Joe Biden remains in his Delaware home recovering from COVID-19 as a growing number of congressional Democrats call for him to exit the presidential race. Pressure is also coming from top donors as polls show a growing number of voters believe the president should end his campaign.
title: Pressure for Biden to exit the race rises

description: The official Xinhua News Agency said five vehicles that fell off the bridge have been recovered after the structure in Shaanxi province crumbled on Friday.
title: At least 11 dead after highway bridge in China collapses

description: Former President Donald Trump returns to the campaign trail today after being officially named the Republican presidential nominee. In Michigan, Trump will hold his first rally since the attempt on his life last weekend, accompanied by vice presidential pick JD Vance.
title: Trump returns to campaign trail after assassination attempt, RNC nomination

description: Companies are seeing signs of recovery this morning after a worldwide computer outage disrupted systems for air travel, health care, banking and more.
title: Recovery continues after global computer outage

description: The authorization does not mean a strike will happen immediately and both sides could reach a deal. If a strike does happen, it would be the first at Disneyland in 40 years.
title: Disneyland workers vote to authorize strike, citing unfair labor practice

description: The biggest continuing effect has been on air travel. Carriers canceled thousands of flights on Friday and now have many of their planes and crews in the wrong place.
title: Airlines, businesses rush to get back on track after global tech disruption

description: The cosmos is providing a full moon for the 55th anniversary of the first lunar landing this weekend, and plenty of other events honor Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin's giant leap.
title: Moon fests, moon movie and full moon mark 55th anniversary of Apollo 11 landing

description: A Connecticut movie theater celebrates employees with disabilities all year by searching for their "sparkle" – their unique talents that they can use at work. Plus, a group of college students use their final exam to help a man in need of a home. And more heartwarming news.
title: The Uplift: Searching for sparkle

description: Novo Nordisk and Lilly can't keep up with demand for their weight loss drugs such as Ozempic, Wegovy and Mounjaro. But they object to specialty pharmacies making their own cheaper versions to fill the gap — providing as much as 30% of those drugs sold in the U.S.
title: Why millions are trying FDA-approved alternatives to Big Pharma's weight loss drugs

description: Historic IT outage causes travel chaos, leaves airlines reeling; 10 years on, unique Nashville friendship built around a weekly high five endures
title: 7/19: CBS Evening News

description: NBA superstars like LeBron James, Steph Curry, Jayson Tatum are on the same team. Find out how to watch.
title: When does Team USA men's basketball play next?

description: Last month, Lee revealed that she had been diagnosed with pancreatic cancer.
title: Sheila Jackson Lee, longtime Texas congresswoman, dies at 74

description: Bob Newhart, whose observational humor and deadpan delivery raised his comedy albums and TV sitcoms to classic status, died on Thursday, July 18, 2024, at the age of 94. In this "Sunday Morning" profile that aired on November 3, 2002, the comedian, recipient of the Mark Twain Prize for American Humor, talked with correspondent Rita Braver about his journey from accounting to standup. Braver also talks with the comic's co-stars Jane Curtin ("The Librarian") and Tom Poston ("Newhart") about Newhart's gifts.
title: From the archives: Bob Newhart

description: Lana Zak reports on the ripple effects of a global technology outage, the latest in the investigation into the assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump, and the 55th anniversary of the Apollo 11 moon landing.
title: 7/19: CBS News Weekender

description: The virtual ballot will show Biden "as the presumptive and only qualified nominee," but  there's an option for delegates to mark their own preference, as there was in 2020.
title: DNC backs virtual roll call vote for Biden as outside groups educate delegates

description: Every week for nearly a decade, Andy Gullahorn goes for a walk, and about a mile-and-a-half away, his friend Gabe Scott does the same thing at the same time. They walk toward each other, and when they meet they high five. Then, they often simply walk home. Steve Hartman has their story.
title: 10 years on, unique Nashville friendship built around a weekly high five endures
